Question

Please write a query for dvdrental database.
Please calculate following information for August 2005:
•	How many movies was rented each day
•	How many unique customers were served each day.
o	If one customer rented 2 movies on the same day, should be counted just once.
Final query should have 3 columns: date, number of movies, number of customers
Sort results by date.

SELECT
	date_trunc('day',rental_date) AS day,
	count(inventory_id) AS number_of_movies,
	count(DISTINCT customer_id) AS number_of_customers
	
FROM public.rental
WHERE date_trunc('day',rental_date) BETWEEN '2005-08-01' AND'2005-08-31'
	  
GROUP BY date_trunc('day',rental_date)
ORDER BY day;
		  
